50|$|Wood was {{considered}} a likely candidate for the United States Supreme Court in an Obama Administration. Speculation {{that she might be}} appointed intensified after Justice <b>David</b> <b>Souter's</b> retirement announcement, and Wood was the first candidate interviewed for the post by President Barack Obama, who met with her at the White House while she was visiting from Chicago. When Justice John Paul Stevens announced that he would retire at the end of October 2010 term, Wood's name was again widely put forward as a likely replacement.|$|R
